external_knowledge:
- 'Top-rated' refers to movies with the highest vote average;
- 'Most pertinent themes' refer to keywords that are most relevant to the movie;
- 'Sought-after actors' refer to actors with the highest popularity scores.

- "golden geese" is a metaphor for highly profitable entities; 
- "high-stakes cinema" refers to movies with significant budgets;
- "golden harvest" symbolizes substantial earnings;
- "financial glory" signifies high average revenue.

sql:
SELECT AVG(revenue) AS average_revenue
FROM movies
WHERE release_date > '2010-01-01' AND vote_count > 500;

SELECT title, revenue
FROM movies
ORDER BY revenue DESC;

SELECT COUNT(c.crew_id) AS crew_count
FROM crews c
WHERE c.name = 'James Cameron' AND c.job = 'Director';
